    {
      "id": "3b1ee24087f57266fd878596ebc0ed2d523c1aff",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-05 20:57:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJeremy, Daniel, Ken, Thomas,\nI don't know enough about this code to inspect it, but I'm happy to land it if someone else with some Kerberos experience gives it a positive review.\n\nIt doesn't introduce any regressions in the non-kerberos code, but we aren't testing Kerberos ourselves.  Seagate has a number of patches to fix this code, so I'd encourage you to help them land it before the 2.7.0 code freeze at the end of January.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "236eba42df21fe0a9c2c0075893218c15bf82caa",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-16 11:44:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2\n\nSince this couldn't break anything besides Kerberos, and that is already non-functional, landing it can't be worse than what we have today.\n\nI'd hoped that there would be more interest from others in reviewing this code.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
